<DIV1 TYPE="account">
<PB N="29" REF="000606_0029_0FA95D36B8C1A1F0">
<HEAD>An Account of our sincere Faith in the most necessary things of Christian Doctrine, Faith and Practice, according to the Testi|mony of holy Scripture. Given forth by some of us, in behalf of many Brethren, who are in scorn called <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">uakers</HI> in <HI>Penn|silvania, &amp;c.</HI> And are the things that we had drawn up to have proposed to their consideration at the Meeting appointed for that end at <HI>S. E</HI>'s the <HI>14</HI> of <HI>3</HI> mon. <HI>1692.</HI> but not suffered to be read there, neither can another Meeting be procured, tho' much desired by us.</HEAD>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;&middot; 1</HI> Of God the Father, the Son and the holy Spirit.</HEAD>
<P>WE believe in <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Epes. 4.4 5&punc; 6. 1 Cor 12.4, 5, 6. Col. 1.16.</NOTE> one God, and in one Lord Jesus Christ, and in one holy Spirit, and that these three are one true God, the make<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> and Creator of all things, visible and invisible. Tha<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> God is no Body, but a pure <NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg">Joh. 4.24 1 Joh. 1.5. Deut. 3.20. Ps. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 47 4 5. Act. 15 18. Ps. 139. 1, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, 6.7. Joh. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">1.17. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">cts 1.24.</NOTE> Spirit, Light and Life, eternal and unchangeable, of infinite Perfection in Wisdom, Goodness, Power, Justice and Holiness, knowing all things, past, present &amp; to come, present in all things, and able to do all things whatsoever he plea|seth. That God hath fore-known <NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. 8.29 30. Eph 1.4 5. 1 Pet. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">.2.</NOTE> all who are or shall be saved, from the beginning of the Wo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ld to the end of it, <HI>having chosen <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> in Christ Iesus before the Foundation of the World, to be holy, and through Holiness and Sanctification of the Spirit unto Eternal Life &amp; Glory.</HI> That as Gods Love &amp; Grace is freely extended unto <NOTE N="d" PLACE="marg"><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Tim. 2.3, 4, 5.</NOTE> all, where<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">y they may be saved, and none are excluded from the possibility of Salvation by any Decree of <HI>absolute Reprobation</HI>; so whoever are o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> shall be saved, from the beginning of the World to the end of it, they are saved by<NOTE N="e" PLACE="marg">Eph. 2.8.</NOTE> <HI>Grace, through Faith, and not o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> themselves, it is the Gift o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> God.</HI> And that not only Christ <NOTE N="f" PLACE="marg"><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> 42, 1, 1 P<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t 2 6,</NOTE> is Gods Elect, but all <NOTE N="g" PLACE="marg">2 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">im <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">.10 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> 9 23 cap <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 7 &amp; 2<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 2<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">&punc; 3<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">&punc; 32, Ephes 1, 4.</NOTE> that shall be saved, from the beginning of the World to the end of it, are Gods <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">lect, chosen in Christ, their Elect Head &amp; Root, as his Elect Body and Mem|bers, according to the F<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">re-knowledge and Counsel of God, not <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> before the believe and repent, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> before the Foundation of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">he World&punc; yet as with respect to mens knowledge, they are said to be God<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Elect who ar<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <HI>sanctified</HI> and <HI>renewed,</HI> o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <HI>born again,</HI> and such are Gods Elect who cry day and night unto him, whom he will avenge, <HI>Luke</HI> 18.7.
<PB N="30" REF="000606_0030_0FA95D36CDF63030">
and who put on, being the Elect of God, holy and beloved, <HI>Bowels of M<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">y, Kindness, Humbleness of Mind, Meekness, Long-Suffering, &amp;c. Col.</HI> 3.12.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 2.</HI> Of Man, before and after the Fall.</HEAD>
<P>That Man consisteth of a <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Isa. 57.16</NOTE> created Soul and Body, and that the Soul of man is neither God nor the Devil, nor any part or measure either of God or the Devil, but an invisible Spirit, endued with Rea|s<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters"> and Understanding, Will, Affections, Memory, and Power of Mo|tion, capable to serve and obey God, by the help of his Grace, and to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">eceive the <NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg">Ro. 6.21, 22. Luk. 1<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 22&punc; 23.</NOTE> Fruit of his Obedience, which is Life; or capable to disobey and transgress, and to receive the fruit of his Disobedience, which is Death. <NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg">Ro. 6.21, 22. Luk. 1<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 22&punc; 23.</NOTE> And that the Soul dyeth not with the Body, but surviveth after it. That God made man upright, after his <NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg">Gen. 1.26 cap. 3.22. 1 Cor. 1<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 2.</NOTE> Image, Male and Female, and gave him dominion over the works of his hands, &amp; gave him a Law, which if he had obey<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">d, he had lived forever. That <NOTE N="d" PLACE="marg"><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">en. 1&punc;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">7 cap. 3.16, 17&punc; 18&punc;19. Rom. 5.12</NOTE> both the Death of the Soul unto Righteousness, and Bodily Sickness and Death came by the Fall of Man, with many other Calamities, <HI>and that by one man sin entred into the World, and Death by sin, &amp;c.</HI> and a seed of sin &amp; defilement is sown by the Enemy in the hearts of <HI>Adams</HI> Poste|rity, but yet that is not imputed to Damnation, but to such only as obey it.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 3.</HI> Of Restoration by Iesus Christ, and Faith in him.</HEAD>
<P>That Jesus Christ is the <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Prov. 8.23, 24. cap 30.4. M<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">c. 5, 6&punc; Jo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 19.<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">5. N<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">h. 9.<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">0. Joh. 15.26.</NOTE> Son of God, and the only begotten of God from Everlasting, and one God with the Father; and that he was the Redeemer and Saviour of all that believed in him from the begin|ning of the World, and gave them the holy Spirit to renew &amp; sanctifie them, and that this holy Spirit did proceed from the Father and from the Son&punc; And that in the fullness of time Christ took on him the <NOTE PLACE="marg">Heb. 2 16 Gal 4.4. Gen. 3.15 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">at 18 20 21 25</NOTE> Seed of <HI>Abraham,</HI> and <HI>was made of a Woman made under the Law,</HI> the promised <HI>Seed of the Woman, that should bruise t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e head of the Serpent,</HI> and was conceived of the holy Ghost, and bo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n of the Virgin <HI>Mary.</HI> That Christ, as Man, had and now hath the true and entire Nature of Man, both of <NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg">Mat 26 38 John 2 19, 20, 21 Col 1 20</NOTE> Soul and Body, and that neither his Soul nor Body is the Go<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">head, but the Temple of it. That he <NOTE N="d" PLACE="marg">Rom <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 25 1 Cor 15 3 4 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"></NOTE> dyed for ou<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> sins, and rose again for our <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ustification, &amp; by the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">lood of his Cross made Peace for us, and was a Sacrifice of Attonement unto God, and a <HI>Prop<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">tia<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ion not or our sins only, but <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">or the sins of the whole World.</HI> That he rose <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ead, and ascended into Heaven without us, in the same Body for <NOTE N="e" PLACE="marg">Rom 6 9 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span">&punc;</NOTE> Be|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">g&punc; which was crucified and buried, but most wonderfully a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">d most
<PB N="31" REF="000606_0031_0FA95D378B22FF78">
gloriously changed in Manner and Condition. And that in the same Body, (<HI>i. e.</HI> a heavenly glorious and immortal Body) he will come and appear without us to judge the quick and the dead. That <NOTE N="f" PLACE="marg">Joh 1 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> 14 16 17 cap 8 24 cap 14 1, 2. Gal 3 26 &amp; 4 5 30 31 1 Joh 4 2 cap 5 1 4 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 6</NOTE> Faith in Christ Jesus as he came without us in the flesh, and dyed for our sins, and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ose again and is gone into Heaven, and there remaineth our Advo|cate and Mediator with the Father, in whom all Fullness of Grace and Truth dwelleth, as well as he doth inwardly come into our hearts to enlighten and quicken us, is necessary to make a true Christian, and to beget us unto God, so as to be his Children, born of the free-woman, <HI>Ier<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">ale<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI> from above; and that without this Faith none can be so born no<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> have the Spirit of Adoption, witnessing to them, that they are the Children of God. That the true <NOTE N="g" PLACE="marg">James <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 14 17 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">0</NOTE> Faith in Christ Jesus, as he dyed for <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> and rose again, is not a ba<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e historical and litteral Faith, such as Hypocrites and false Christians have, but is a living and faithful Faith, conforming them wh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> have it to Christ Jesus, to live &amp; walk as he did, and that this Faith is wrought in all who have it by the <HI>VVord of</HI> <NOTE N="h" PLACE="marg">Rom 10 8 9 2 Cor. 4 13 Col 2 12.</NOTE> <HI>Faith in the Heart,</HI> and by the <HI>Spirit of Faith,</HI>