P DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">or, and doth reprove for <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">in &amp; disobedience, and bringeth the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> under the Law, &amp; Ministration thereof, which is of a sa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">ing nature &amp; tendenc<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> in a general way; and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> <NOTE N="m" PLACE="marg">Gal 3 24</NOTE> <HI>Schoolmaster to bring men</HI> (who gi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">d to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t) <HI>to Christ,</HI> th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t they might be justified by Faith. That none who are <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ince<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e, according to the <NOTE N="n" PLACE="marg">Mark 4 2<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Joh 3 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> Jam 4 6 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> 5 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> 10 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 9 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">il <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Act <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">0 4 35</NOTE> least measure of Light given to th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">, if the continue to fo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">low the Lord, can fall short of eternal Life and Salvation; for he will lead them from one degree of Light &amp;
<PB N="32" REF="000606_0032_0FA95D384D601E38">
Grace to another, (as he led <HI>Israel</HI> of old out of <HI>Egypt,</HI> through the red Sea, and the Wilderness, and through <HI>Iordan,</HI> unto the promised Land) until he who hath begun his good Work of Salvation in them, bring it to Perfection. That <NOTE N="o" PLACE="marg">Rom 10 8 9 Deutr 30 14 15 Heb 7 25 26 Mat 1 21 1 Tim 2 5</NOTE> Christ the <HI>VVord</HI> and the <HI>Light</HI> is in every man (tho' not revealed or known as such) and is sufficient to save every man, but Christ whole and undivided is our all-sufficient Saviour, <HI>able to save to the uttermost all that come unto God by him</HI>; and as Christ without us, as he dyed and rose again, and is ascended, and is our Me|diator with God in Heaven, doth not save us without Christ in us, so nor doth Christ in us save us without Christ without us, the which Christ is one, the fullness<NOTE N="p" PLACE="marg">Joh 1 15 16</NOTE> without us in the Man Christ Jesus, and the mea|sure of him in us; &amp; the <NOTE N="q" PLACE="marg">Eph 4 7 13 16 Cant 5 4 Mat 3 12</NOTE> measure of the heavenly Gift of Christ work|eth savingly in us, by the Power &amp; Strength of the Fullness; and none witness Christ perfectly to save them, but who have <NOTE N="r" PLACE="marg">Rom 10 8 9 10 Joh 3 14 15 36 cap 12 36</NOTE> Faith in him as he dyed and rose again, and is gone into Heaven, and there remaineth our Advocate and Mediator, as well as that they believe in him as he is spiritually present in them, to enlighten, quicken &amp; Sanctifie them. That as the sufficiency of Christs Light and Grace within every man is not to be set up in opposition to Christ without us, who hath all full|ness of Light, Grace and Truth dwelling in him, <HI>and o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ose</HI> <NOTE N="s" PLACE="marg">Joh 1 15 15 Mark 4 25 2 Cor 8 9 James 4 6 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> 1 2</NOTE> <HI>Full|ness we all receive Grace <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> Grace;</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">or is the present measure of Light and Grace received, to be set in opposition to f<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">der measures of Light &amp; Grace yet to be received. And th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Sufficiency that any hath o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Grace, is for the present time, but not for all time to come; and therefore every one is to wait <NOTE N="t" PLACE="marg">Isa 4<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 29 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">1</NOTE> in the present measure already recei|ved, and by the help of the same to pray to God in <NOTE N="u" PLACE="marg">J<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">hn 14, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">3&punc; cap 16 23&punc; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">4. Mat 7, 7.8, Col 2, 3,</NOTE> <HI>the Name of Christ Iesus,</HI> to receive a daily and hourly supply from God, out of Christs fullness (as out of a most rich Treasury and Store-house) of more Grace, that so <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e who hath began his good work in them,</HI> having given them a small measure of his Grace, <HI>may carry it on in them to perfection,</HI> by his giving them a daily supply and <HI>encrease of more Grace,</HI> which they shall all receive, as they <HI>wait</HI> and <HI>pray</HI> for it, being found in all diligent <HI>Obedience</HI> unto his present requirings.</P>
