<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 4.</HI> Concerning Iustification and Sanctification.</HEAD>
<P>That <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Acts 13, 19&punc; cap 26 18. Heb 5 9&punc; Ro. 5.1</NOTE> <HI>Faith, Repentance, Love, Hope, &amp;c.</HI> and <HI>sincere Obedience to Gods Commands,</HI> altho' they are <HI>necessary Conditions</HI> &amp; <HI>Qualifications</HI> re|quired, in order to our <HI>I<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">st<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">fication</HI> and <HI>Remission of sin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">,</HI> yet they are not the Foundation of it, but <HI>Christ alone</HI> i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> the <HI>fo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ndation</HI> thereof, <HI>in whose Name,</HI> as he dyed for us and rose again, <NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg"><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> 4, 12. 1 Cor 3.11</NOTE> <HI>Repentance and Remission of
<PB N="33" REF="000606_0033_0FA95D391B10C5A0">
sin <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> to be preached,</HI> and <HI>through Faith in his Name,</HI> his <NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg">Luke <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters"> 46, 47.</NOTE> <HI>Obedience</HI> and <HI>Righteousness,</HI> as he dyed for us, and became <HI>obedient unto the death of the Cross,</HI> is <NOTE N="d" PLACE="marg">Rom 3, 24 cap 4, 5, 6, 7 11, Rom 5 16, 18, 19 Phil. 3, 8, 9, 10. Rom 8.34.</NOTE> <HI>imputed</HI> or <HI>accounted to us for Remission of sin</HI> &amp; <HI>Iustification.</HI> <NOTE N="e" PLACE="marg">1 Cor 6, 9, 10, 11,</NOTE> And none are justified but who are sanctified. That tho' there is a <NOTE N="f" PLACE="marg">Luk. 8, 3,</NOTE> <HI>Faith that may be lost</HI> &amp; <HI>fallen from,</HI> yet there is a <HI>degree</HI> in<NOTE N="g" PLACE="marg"><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Pet. 1, 7,</NOTE> <HI>Faith</HI> and <HI>Sanctification,</HI> which the Soul having attained, doth not <HI>lose</HI> nor <HI>fall from</HI> it, and that is the <HI>Faith that is more precious than Gold that perisheth, which being tryed with the fire, endureth to the end of all Temptations.</HI> That a <NOTE N="h" PLACE="marg">Mat 12.20, Rom 6 18 22, cap 8, 2, 3.</NOTE> Victory over sin, and a freedom from it, is <HI>possible</HI> to be obtained by the <HI>Grace of God,</HI> here in this mortal Body, the which Victory and Freedom is not receiv'd nor witnessed <NOTE N="i" PLACE="marg">Phil 2, 12, and 1, 6.</NOTE> all at once, but gradually, and the sooner it is witnessed that men are the more diligent in the impro|vement of Gods Grace, and all helps and means that God hath given us for the same; and it is most safe for all to have a holy jealousie over themselves, that they exceed not in thinking of themselves above what is convenient, but to follow the Example of <HI>Paul,</HI> who said,<NOTE N="k" PLACE="marg">1 Cor 4, 4.</NOTE> <HI>I know no|thing by my self, yet I am not hereby satisfied, but he t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">at judgeth me is the Lord</HI>; and of <HI>Iob,</HI> who said, <HI>Tho I were Perefect, yet would I not know my So<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">l.</HI><NOTE PLACE="marg">Job 9, 21.</NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 5.</HI> Concerning the true Worship of God, and the true Ministry.</HEAD>
<P>That <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Mat 4 10 1 Cor 1, 2, 3 1 Tim 1, 12 Rev 1, 4, 5. Acts 7, 59. Ephe. 6 18.</NOTE> God and Ch<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ist, and the holy Spirit, are only to be Wor|shipped, and Prayed unto, as <HI>on<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">tire Object o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Wo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ship, Prayer</HI> &amp; <HI>Thaaks-giving</HI>; and that all <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> <HI>Wo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">sh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">p, Prayer</HI> &amp; <HI>Thanks-giving</HI> is to be per|form<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">d by the <NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg">Rom 8.26 John 4, 24. 1 Cor 12.3 cap. 14, 15,</NOTE> <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> Gods Spirit,</HI> as it is inwardly <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">elt to move and enable unto the same; and that this <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">elp is to be waited for in true Si|lence and Stillness, from all our own Thoughts, and all Self-movings, and Self-strivings and Workings in the meer Will and Power of man. That none are true Ministers of Christ, but who are <NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg">1 Tim 3, 2 3, 4, Tit 1 7, 8, 9. Mat 10, 8. 2 Cor 11.7</NOTE> <HI>holy men who speak as they are moved by the holy Spirit,</HI> and are qualified &amp; endued with sound knowledge, power &amp; virtue; &amp; that the Gospel is to be preacht freely, without requiring or exacting any thing for the same.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 6.</HI> Concerning the Commandments of God and Christ, and the holy Scriptures.</HEAD>
<P>That besides the general Commandments of God, of <HI>Piety, Iustice</HI> &amp; <HI>Temperance,</HI> given under the Law, briefly contained, for matter and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">bstance, in the <HI>Ten Commandments,</HI> the <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Rom. 2, 15,</NOTE> work or effect of which is writ on the hearts of all men, there are some <HI>special Precepts</HI> and <HI>Com|mandments</HI> of God and Christ given to us under the <HI>New-Testament,</HI> as <HI>Not</HI> <NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg">mat 5 34 cap 19, 5, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, Heb <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">, 9 1 Joh 3 23 Jer 31, 33. Heb <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, 1<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">phe. 2, 7,</NOTE> <HI>to Swear at all, Not to fight with Carnal Weapons, Not to pay
<PB N="34" REF="000606_0034_0FA95D3AB9AC8E90">
Tythes, nor to practise any part of the Ceremonial Law, nor to have more VVives than one at one time</HI>; and also to believe the Doctrine of Christ, as deliver'd by Christ &amp; his holy Prophets and Apostles, in all the parts of it, and recorded in the holy Scriptures. And the whole Law of God, teaching all Duties of <HI>Love</HI> and <HI>Obedience,</HI> is after a more excellent and powerful manner, writ in the hearts of true Christians and sincere Be|lievers in Christ Jesus, than as it is generally writ in the hearts of all Mankind, because the Gospel Dispensation, in the clea<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Ministration of it, through Faith in Christ Jesus, hath more plenty of <HI>Grace, Power</HI> and <HI>Li<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e attending it.</HI> That the holy <NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg"><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Tim 3&punc; 16 1 Tim 4.<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, 1<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">.15 2 C<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> 3.6. Luk 24 4 1 Cor 2 2<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> 1 17 18 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">.9, 18. 1 Joh 5 9 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">0.</NOTE> <HI>Scriptures are given <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ort<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">y di|vine Inspiration,</HI> and are profitable and worthy to be read and meditated upon by the help of the holy Spirit that gave them forth, and that fre|quently, for our <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> &amp; <HI>Com<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ort,</HI> &amp; <HI>encrease of Faith.</HI> That the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> of Scripture as the <HI>Word of God</HI>; that they can only be <HI>savingly understood</HI> by the <HI>illumination</HI> &amp; <HI>revelation</HI> of that Spirit that gave them forth; That they are useful to Believers, for their growth and encreas<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> in Faith and Holiness, and to Unbelievers, that they may believe, as God shall be pleased to make them Instrumental to the same; and that they contain a full and sufficient Testimony to all <HI>Christian Doctrine</HI> &amp; <HI>Practice</HI>; and that the Truth of them is believed principally for and because of the <HI>inward Testimony, Evidence</HI> &amp; <HI>Word o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> God,</HI> and of <HI>the holy Spirit,</HI> sealing to the Truth of them in our hearts; and that they are the only outward Test, Touch-stone &amp; Rule, whereby to try all <HI>Doctrines of men,</HI> so that whatever Doctrine is not according to the holy Scripture, in matters of Faith and Life, is to be rejected and denyed.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 7.</HI> Concerning the Future States of Men after Death, the Day of Iudgment, and Resurrection of the Dead.</HEAD>
<P>That after <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Heb 9, 27 Luk 16, 22, Phil 1, 23, Rev 6.10.11.16.23,</NOTE> Death cometh Judgment, and that the Souls of all true Believers in Christ Jesus, both Males and Females, immediately after Death go to God, and to Christ, in Heaven; and that the Souls of them who dye in <HI>final Impenitency</HI> are cast into <NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg">Psal 9, 17, Rev 2<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, 15</NOTE> Hell. That there is a <HI>General Day</HI> <NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg">Jude 6, 2 P<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t 2.4, mat 7.22, cap 25 3<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, 2 Thes 1, 7, 8.9 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">0: Acts 17 31 Rom 12 10 2 Cor <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"></NOTE> <HI>of Iudgment</HI> yet to come, wherein <HI>all Nations shall stand be<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ore the Son of Man,</HI> even the Man Ch<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ist Jesus, at his <HI>Appear|ance</HI> and <HI>Coming</HI> without us, as well as at his Appearance and Judgment Seat within us, to receive according to the D<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">eds done in the body, good or evil. That Christ is the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">viour o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> who<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e Man, both <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">oul</HI> &amp; <HI>Body</HI>; and that there shall be a <HI>R<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">s<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">rection of the</HI> <NOTE N="d" PLACE="marg"><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> 3 21 mat <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> 28, 1 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> 14 cap 15 20.21.22, 42, 43, 44,</NOTE> <HI>Body, both o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> the Iust and Vnjust,</HI> the Just unto Everlasting Life, and the Unjust unto
<PB N="35" REF="000606_0035_0FA95D3B857F0F08">
shame and Torment forever; and that the <NOTE N="e" PLACE="marg">mat 22, 30, Acts 26.23, 1 Cor 15, 23, 50,</NOTE> Resurrection of the Body is not received in this mortal Life, nor immediately after Death, but the deceased Saints generally wait for it, until the Coming of Christ, and that <HI>the dead in Christ shall rise first,</HI> when the Body that is sown natural shall be raised spiritual; <HI>for Flesh and Blood doth not inherit the Kingdom of God, nor Corruption Incorruption.</HI></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 8.</HI> Concerning Christs Baptism and Supper.</HEAD>
<P>That <HI>Christs</HI> <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">mat 3 11</NOTE> <HI>Baptism</HI> is with the holy Ghost and Fi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e, whereof the outward Baptism with Water was a Figure, the which Fire burneth up the Dross and Combustible matter of the Sins and Lusts that war against the Soul, and is that <NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg">Isa 4 4.</NOTE> Spirit of judgment and of Burning, by which the Filth of the Daughter of <HI>Zion</HI> is to be purged away. That Christs <NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg">Joh 6.53, 5<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 55, 56, 1 Cor 16.17. Rev 3.20, 1 Cor 11, 24, 25 26&punc;</NOTE> <HI>Supper</HI> is his feeding all the faithful, with giving them his flesh to eat, and his Blood to drink, and such have eternal Life in them, and they daily remember and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">editate on the <HI>Lords Death,</HI> by the help of his Spirit in them, until his <HI>Last Coming in the Clouds of Heaven,</HI> with|out them, as well as until his more a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">undant Revelation in them, and that it is their Duty, as well as great spiritual advantage, to remember him mo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> frequently, with <HI>Prayer</HI> and <HI>Thanks-giving,</HI> both when they eat not, and when they eat, whether more privately or more solmenly, as occasion offers.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 9</HI> Concerning Places and Times of Worship, &amp;c.</HEAD>
<P>That all <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">John 4 21.22.23, 1 Tim 2 8, Col 2.16&punc;</NOTE> <HI>Places</HI> and <HI>Times</HI> of <HI>Worship,</HI> in themselves considered, are alike under the Gospel for the Worship of God, and no Place or Time is more Holy than another, yet convenient Places and Times of Worship, with other necessary Circumstances, are to be regarded; and the First Day of the Week is worthily set apart from Bodily Labour, for (<HI>b</HI>) Religious Duties and Exercises, both in publick and private, as well as other convenient times on Week Days, and for meeting to|gether to wait upon God both in Silence, and in the performance of any outward Exercise of Religion, that his Spirit moveth unto.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 10.</HI> Concerning some other Necessary Things.</HEAD>
<P>That <HI>Plain</HI> <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Col 4.6. 1 Pet 3, 3, 4, 5, Tit 2 2, 4, Rom 12 2.</NOTE> <HI>Language</HI> and <HI>Plain Habit,</HI> with all manner of <HI>Tem|p<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rance</HI> &amp; <HI>A<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">stinence from all vain Customs o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> the World,</HI> after the manner of the <HI>p<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">imitive Christians, (b)</HI> and according to the Testimony of our An<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ient Brethren, is to be preserved among us, and whatever is of good Report. That all due care is to be taken concerning Marriages, that Persons concern'd may proceed orderly, &amp; that none marry with|in these <NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg">Exod 20, 19. 1 Cor&punc; 5 1</NOTE> degrees of Kindred, forbidden under the Law, which are also forbidden under the Gospel</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="section">
<PB N="36" REF="000606_0036_0FA95D3C0A19C8F0">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 11.</HI> Concerning the Church, and the Qualifications of the True Members thereof.</HEAD>
<P>That the <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Act. 2.49 Rom 10 8, 9, 10, Jam 2.18. 1 Joh 4.2, 3. mat 10&punc; 32, 33.</NOTE> Church of Christ is the multitude of sincere Believers i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">hrist, who ought to manifest their Faith to one another by the living Confession of the Mouth, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">lowing from the living Faith in the Heart, accompanied with the Seal and Confirmation of a Holy and Christian Life and Conversation, which will be sensi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ly <NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg">Gal 2.9. Prov 14 7 Phil 1, 5, 2, 1. Acts 8, 37, John 10, 1, 2, 3 Isa. 44.5. mat 3.6. Act. 19 38. John 9 22, cap 12 42, 2 Cor. 9.13 1 Tim 2, 10, cap 6 12, Heb 3 1, cap 4 14&punc; &amp; 1<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 23</NOTE> discerned through a spiritual inward Gif<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> of Disce<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ning in them, as <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">he Tree is known by the Fruits, and such have a spiritual Fe<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">lowship and Com|munion together in the Spi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">it of Christ, and in th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Gifts, and Graces, and Comforts, and Refreshments thereof, that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">low from <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">st the Head and Fountain, through Member to Member; and is Ch<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t be|lieved in, is the Door into the Church, in the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ight of God, so Christ, both believed and confessed unto, is the D<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">or into the Church in the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ight of men. And that in the Church of Christ, the holy Ghost mak|eth <NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg">Acts 20, 28&punc;</NOTE> Over-seers, Elders and Rulers, who are known, received and owned to be such by the <NOTE N="d" PLACE="marg">2 Cor 4.2, cap 5, 11,</NOTE> Manifestation of the same Spirit in all the true Members thereof.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="12" TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>&sect;. 12.</HI> Concerning Magistracy, and Obedience thereunto.</HEAD>
<P>That it is the Duty of all Christians, to give all ready Obedience to Magistrates in all lawful things, and to be subject to their Commands, <HI>not only for Wrath, but for</HI> <NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Rom. 13, 2&punc; 3 4, 5, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Pet 2, 13 14, 15,</NOTE> <HI>Conscience sake</HI>; and if they command things unlawful, to make no resistance by outward Force, but patiently to suffer under them, for Magistracy and Government in the World is the Ordinance of God, and when d<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ely performed, according to Truth and Righteousness among men, belongeth <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o that universal Mi|nistration of the Spi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">it, given in general to Mankind, by virtue of which, whatever is lawfully commanded by Magistrates, will be an|swered by the Light of God, and that just Principle of God in every mans Conscience, that will lead and instruct him to obey the same.</P>
<CLOSER><HI>Given forth in our own Behalf, and in behalf of many Brethren, who 
are of the same Faith, By us,</HI> 
